message.content: Santa Cruz is a city located in Monterey County, California. It is known for its beautiful beaches, surfing culture, and scenic coastline. The city has a population of approximately 56,700 people and is the county seat of Monterey County. Santa Cruz has a rich history that includes Native American settlements, Spanish exploration, and Mexican rule. It became an incorporated city in 1867 and was named after the biblical figure St. Francis Xavier. The city's economy relies on tourism, fishing, and agriculture. Some of the main attractions in Santa Cruz include the Beach Boardwalk, Natural Bridges State Park, and the famous surf spot, Steep Bank.
